"title": "5702: husband",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5702",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The male partner in a marriage relationship. The origin of this God-ordained institution is traced back in the Bible to the Garden of Eden. Scripture stresses that marriage is a God-ordained institution, within which the husband is pledged to love and care for his wife. Scripture contains many examples, both good and bad, of how husbands behaved. The ultimate examples of a good husband in Scripture are God as the husband of Israel and Jesus Christ as the bridegroom of the church.</p>\n<h2>God's pattern for marriage</h2>\n<h3>Husband and wife are one flesh</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:27\">GEN 1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:23-Gen2:24\">GEN 2:23–2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:15\">MAL 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:4-Matt19:6\">MAT 19:4–19:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:6-Mark10:9\">MRK 10:6–10:9</a></p>\n<h3>The husband is head of the wife</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:23\">EPH 5:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:3\">1CO 11:3</a></p>\n<h2>Duties of a husband</h2>\n<h3>To leave his parents and be united to his wife</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:5\">MAT 19:5</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:7-Mark10:8\">MRK 10:7–10:8</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:24\">GEN 2:24</a></p>\n<h3>To love his wife</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25\">EPH 5:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:5\">DEU 24:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:18\">PRO 5:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:9\">ECC 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:28-Eph5:33\">EPH 5:28–5:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:19\">COL 3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:7\">1PE 3:7</a></p>\n<h3>To fulfil his marital duty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:3-1Cor7:5\">1CO 7:3–7:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:10-Exod21:11\">EXO 21:10–21:11</a></p>\n<h3>To be faithful to his wife</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:14\">EXO 20:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:18\">DEU 5:18</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:10\">LEV 20:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:22\">DEU 22:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:14\">MAL 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:27-Matt5:28\">MAT 5:27–5:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:14-1Cor7:16\">1CO 7:14–7:16</a></p>\n<h2>Adam, the first husband</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:20-Gen2:24\">GEN 2:20–2:24</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Behaviour which is commended in husbands</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:3-1Sam1:8\">1SA 1:3–1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:67\">GEN 24:67</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:20\">GEN 29:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth3:7-Ruth4:11\">RUT 3:7–4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:1-Esth5:3\">EST 5:1–5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:1-Hos3:3\">HOS 3:1–3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:18-Matt1:25\">MAT 1:18–1:25</a></p>\n<h2>Behaviour which is condemned in husbands</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:7-2Sam12:10\">2SA 12:7–12:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:30-Gen29:31\">GEN 29:30–29:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:8-Gen38:10\">GEN 38:8–38:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:16-Judg19:29\">JDG 19:16–19:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:13-Mal2:16\">MAL 2:13–2:16</a></p>\n<h2>God as a husband</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:5\">ISA 54:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:14\">JER 3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:32\">JER 31:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:8\">EZK 16:8</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as a bridegroom</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:27\">EPH 5:25–5:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:14-Matt9:15\">MAT 9:14–9:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:18-Mark2:20\">MRK 2:18–2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:33-Luke5:35\">LUK 5:33–5:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:2\">2CO 11:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:2\">REV 21:2</a></p>",
